# Not tracked: the fixtures rely on object-database state that depends on the
# host (auto-gc/auto-repack thresholds, alternates pointing at absolute paths)
# and so cannot be reproduced reliably from a committed archive.

# `make_alternates_odb.sh` writes `$PWD/object_source/.git/objects` into
# `.git/objects/info/alternates`; the absolute path is host-specific.
make_alternates_odb.tar
# Fixture deliberately uses loose objects; whether commits remain loose vs. get
# packed depends on the host git's auto-gc/repack defaults, so the layout is
# regenerated per run.
repo_with_loose_objects.tar
